<doc id="272078" wikidata="Q2233125" url="?curid=272078" title="Pilanesberg International Airport">
<text>Pilanesberg International Airport is an airport serving Sun City in the North West province of South Africa. It is located adjacent to the Pilanesberg National Park.

==Facilities==
The airport resides at an elevation of above mean sea level. It has one runway designated 05/23 with an asphalt surface measuring .

==Communication==
The Communication Frequency for Pilanesberg International Airport is 118.40 MHz.
Runway lights can be activated by making 3-7 clicks on 118.40 MHz.
The control tower can be contacted on +27 (0)14 55 22154.

==Nearby airports==
* Lanseria International Airport
* Rustenburg Airfield

==See also==
* Pilanesberg
* Pilanesberg National Park
* Sun City

